{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:24:22.718110+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here’s a walkthrough of the database migrations in **rpnr-bench/T11_R01**, in the order they are applied.\n\n---\n\n## How migrations are applied\n\nThe script [`scripts/apply_migrations.sh`](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T11_R01/blob/main/scripts/apply_migrations.sh) iterates over `migrations/*.sql` in **lexicographic (filename glob) order** and feeds each file to the PostgreSQL container (`pgdev_db`) via `docker exec`.  \nBecause the files are numbered `001`, `002`, `003`, they run sequentially in that order.\n\n---\n\n## Migration 1 – `001_create_users.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE users (\n    id           BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    email        TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n    display_name TEXT,\n    created_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**What it does:**  \nCreates the `users` table, the core identity store.\n\n- `id` – Auto-incrementing `BIGINT` primary key (PostgreSQL `BIGSERIAL`).  \n- `email` – Unique, not-null text column. Serves as the login/contact identifier.  \n- `display_name` – Optional display name (nullable).  \n- `created_at` – Timestamp with time zone, defaults to `now()` at insert time.\n\n---\n\n## Migration 2 – `002_create_sessions.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE sessions (\n    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n    user_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    issued_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL\n);\n```\n\n**What it does:**  \nCreates the `sessions` table to manage authenticated user sessions.\n\n- `id` – A `UUID` primary key (session token value).  \n- `user_id` – Foreign key to `users(id)` with `ON DELETE CASCADE` (when a user is deleted, all their sessions are removed).  \n- `issued_at` – When the session was created, defaults to `now()`.  \n- `expires_at` – Required timestamp defining when the session expires (enforced application-side).\n\n---\n\n## Migration 3 – `003_add_session_index.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);\n```\n\n**What it does:**  \nAdds a B-tree index on `sessions.user_id`. This speeds up queries that look up all sessions belonging to a particular user (e.g., listing active sessions, or checking for existing sessions during login). Without this index, every such lookup would require a full sequential scan of the `sessions` table.\n\n---\n\n## Summary table\n\n| Order | File                          | Action                                                         |\n|-------|-------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|\n| 1     | `001_create_users.sql`        | Create `users` table (id, email, display_name, created_at).    |\n| 2     | `002_create_sessions.sql`     | Create `sessions` table (id, user_id FK → users, issued_at, expires_at). |\n| 3     | `003_add_session_index.sql`   | Create index `idx_sessions_user_id` on `sessions(user_id)`.    |\n\nThere are no further migrations beyond these three. Separately, the repository also contains seed data in [`seeds/001_dev_users.sql`](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T11_R01/blob/main/seeds/001_dev_users.sql) that can be applied after migrations to populate development rows, but that is not a migration itself.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 781, "prompt_tokens": 5482, "total_tokens": 6263, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 13, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 5120}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 5120, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 362}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "452699ad-d5de-4213-a85e-cb80d19f26f7", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f8-d918-7581-8616-be3b6a1f88e2-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5482, "output_tokens": 781, "total_tokens": 6263, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 5120}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 13}}}}]}}}
